    "Id": "chassisdef_cockroach_CRH-2B",
    "Name": "Cockroach",
    "Details": "Created to provide armor and firepower on the cheap, the Ironclad is marketed to militias and planetary defence forces unable to afford the maintenance costs of operating a fusion powered battlemech. Manufactured by Heavy Duty Galatea in 3041, the Ironclad IC-100 has since become a staple of the Galatean Defence Force and has made inroads into Lyran space. Powered by a 200 rated Fuel Cell Engine, the Ironclad is a slow and ponderous mountain of armor and guns. A pair of Gauss Rifles provide heavy ranged fire while a battery of Medium and Small Lasers paired with a trio of Small Pulse Lasers shred enemies that attempt to close in.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Reinforced Structure</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.14</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_ironclad"
  },
  "VariantName": "CRH-2B",
